                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.24/34: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dwyre</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-07-05T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 5, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. Your no. 46, June 28, 3 p.m. No formal statement is required for the purposes
                    outlined in the Department’s circular telegram of June 27 but merely an informal
                    indication of the attitude of the Uruguayan Government. Most of the replies have
                    now been received and have all been favorable and the Department hopes that the
                    views of the Uruguayan Government can be indicated, as above, at an early
                    date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
